channel.title: Red Hat Issue Tracker
channel.description: This file is an XML representation of an issue

item.title: [SWATCH-3809] Investigate tally increase on RHEL ELS longrun test account
item.description:
Unexpected tally increase appeared on 21st of July, and test showed 47 vCPUs and not the expected 24. When looking at that day on 23rd of July, it shows 69 vCPUs.

>       assert tally.get("value") == expected_vcpus
E       AssertionError: assert 47 == 24
E        +  where 47 = <built-in method get of dict object at 0x7f1b7896cdc0>('value')
E        +    where <built-in method get of dict object at 0x7f1b7896cdc0> = {'date': datetime.datetime(2025, 7, 21, 0, 0, tzinfo=tzlocal()), 'has_data': True, 'value': 47}.get

ENV: Stage

Ibutsu
item.summary: Investigate tally increase on RHEL ELS longrun test account

status.description: The issue is closed. See the resolution for context regarding why (for example Done, Abandoned, Duplicate, etc)

comments.comment:
Closing this, because the action for this card was "Investigate".  Investigation is done and I've confirmed that the behavior described in this card is caused by SWATCH-3545.

The bug has significant potential impact on billing calculations and could create cascading effects, the current scope is limited to the stage environment due to specific test conditions.

The production environment is effectively protected by natural time separation and the absence of automated test interference.

However, the bug represents a real risk that should be addressed proactively, as future changes to production patterns (increased manual API usage, configuration changes, high-load situations) could potentially trigger the same conditions.

I've elevated SWATCH-3545 priority and the fix is in progress.
